An Android Developer is responsible for designing, developing, and maintaining mobile applications for devices running the Android operating system.

🔧 Key Responsibilities
Develop and maintain Android applications using Android Studio
Write clean and efficient code in Java and Kotlin
Design intuitive and user-friendly UI/UX
Integrate APIs and third-party libraries
Debug, test, and optimize application performance
Ensure app compatibility across different Android devices
Collaborate with designers, backend developers, and product teams
🛠️ Required Skills
Strong knowledge of Android SDK
Understanding of REST API integration
Experience with databases (SQLite, Firebase)
Knowledge of version control tools like Git
Familiarity with MVC/MVVM architecture
🎓 Qualifications
Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or related field
Experience in mobile app development (internships/projects)
💼 Optional (Bonus Skills)
Knowledge of Flutter or cross-platform tools
Experience with publishing apps on Google Play Store
Understanding of performance optimization and security
